<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>

<script>
function myFunction(container) {
  container.innerHTML = "Hello World";
}
</script>

</head>

<body onload="myFunction(document.getElementById('test'))">

<h1>The onload Event</h1>

<p>The onload event is used launch the script passed .</p>

<p>using a div with id=test which  we passed by document.getElementById().</p>




<div id="test"></div>





</body>
</html>